Indonesia's consumption of orange is merely 2.69 kg/ capita/ year and its total fruit consumption is only 34.55 kg/ capita/ year while the standard from FAO is 75 kg/ capita/ year (Republika Online, 2016)

ORIGAMI is an event held by Himpunan Mahasiswa Teknologi Hasil Pertanian Universitas Brawijaya to celebrate World Food Day.
